 3 │ Debugging performance issues in production can feel like chasing ghosts. You’ve got alerts, metrics, and logs, but pinpointing the *why* behind the slowdown is often a frustrating, iterative process. I recently experienced this firsthand with a seemingly innocuous memory leak plaguing one of our long-running Node.js worker processes – a process that was handling a significant chunk of our real-time data processing. The journey from initial alerts to identifying the root cause felt like navigating a complex maze, and it highlighted some crucial lessons about monitoring, debugging, and event listener management.
   ·                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               ───┬───
