    ╭─[corpus/llm/blog/19f12335d308d0e0.md:33:46]
 32 │ 
 33 │ The solution was surprisingly simple – yet incredibly common. We implemented a robust cleanup mechanism within the event listener that ensured all associated objects were released from the heap after each processed message. This involved explicitly calling `delete` on the message object and potentially triggering garbage collection to help clear out unused memory. 
    ·                                            ─────┬────
    ·                                                 ╰── "incredibly" reads as machine-favored register (mined llm-favored (MINING.md); very is the plain intensifier); "very" is a plain near-synonym
